definition: to get rid of/to remove/to exclude/to eliminate/to wipe out/to divide/except/not including

sentences.english: In an hour we strain the first broth off.
sentences.chinese: 一小時後我們濾除第一鍋湯。

sentences.english: A new method for prestack coherent noise elimination is put forward here.
sentences.chinese: 本文提出了一種新的疊前相干干擾濾除方法。

sentences.english: Attack response generation refers to the process of generating rules to filter out attack traffic.
sentences.chinese: 攻擊響應生成涉及生成規則來濾除攻擊流量的過程。

sentences.english: A second drawback of a pure device is that it does not filter any redundant state changes.
sentences.chinese: 純設備的第二個缺點是它不會濾除任何冗餘狀態變化。

sentences.english: The lenses can filter out ultra-violet rays.
sentences.chinese: 這個鏡片可以濾除紫外線。

sentences.english: Desalination membranes filter out salts, allowing clean water to pass through.
sentences.chinese: 脫鹽膜可濾除鹽份，讓清的水流過。

sentences.english: The median filter has good effect in filtering the noise.
sentences.chinese: 中值濾波器在濾除椒鹽噪聲方面效果很好。

sentences.english: We must filter out the dirt.
The suspending impurities above 5 um will be sieved effectively .
sentences.chinese: 有效濾除5微米以上的懸浮微粒雜質。

sentences.english: This time-out period filters any short input-voltage transients.
sentences.chinese: 這個延時時間濾除了所有輸入電壓的毛刺。
